<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
CONSTRUCTION BEGINS ON 25-ACRE PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT LAWRENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Rancho Simi Recreation and Parks District has begun construction of the 
25-acre Rancho Madera Community Park and is expanding its 10-acre Rancho Tapo 
Community Park. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Madera Park, at Wood Ranch Parkway and Lake Park Drive, will include a 
softball diamond, soccer field and a perimeter walkway. 
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the park construction will cost about $1 million, with money 
coming from developers' fees and the park district's general fund, parks 
spokesman Rick Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Tapo Park, at Avenida Simi and Lemon Street, will be expanded by six 
acres. Completion of the two parks will cost $3.2 million, Johnson said. SCOTT 
LAWRENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Bulldozers clear way for new Rancho Madera Community Park in Simi 
Valley. DEBRA MYRENT / For The Times 
</P>
