<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SIMI VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
MAYOR, RESIDENT FILE FOR ELECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Simi Valley Mayor Greg Stratton and resident Alfred J. Wilson have filed papers 
to run for mayor in November, city officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The deadline for filing for the mayor's race is 5 p.m. today, said Alice 
Redondo, assistant city clerk. 
</P>
<P>
Six others have filed to run for two City Council seats. They are Councilwoman 
Ann Rock, seeking her third term; Planning Commissioner Judy Mikels; Simi 
Valley High School teacher Bruce Kanegai; businessman Dave McCormick; resident 
Harold Fick; and community activist John Etter. 
</P>
<P>
Councilwoman Vicky Howard, whose term expires in November, is running for 
Ventura County supervisor against fellow Councilman Bill Davis, whose term 
expires in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
Those who have taken out council papers but have not yet filed include 
neighborhood activist Marilyn Maurer, Chamber of Commerce member Sandi Webb and 
residents Kenneth Wenning and David Meichtry. 
</P>
<P>
The filing deadline for the two council seats is Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
In the race for two open seats on the Simi Valley Board of Education, Lew Roth, 
a 22-year board veteran, and Simi Valley High School counselor Carla Kurachi 
have filed to run in November. Board President Helen Beebe said she will not 
seek reelection. 
</P>
<P>
Residents Michael Murray and Karolyn Searight have been issued nomination 
papers but have not filed, district officials said. School board candidates 
also have until Wednesday to file. CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
