<HEADLINE>
<P>
CUTTING WATER USE AND DWP LEAKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We in Los Angeles have just survived July, the hottest month in recorded 
history. 
</P>
<P>
Our lawns and plants are dying of thirst. Yet, despite these obstacles, we 
nearly achieved our 10% water conservation goal, missing by only two-tenths of 
one percent (9.8%). 
</P>
<P>
Still the Department of Water and Power and Mayor Tom Bradley feel the need of 
brandishing the club of mandatory rationing (Part B, Aug. 3). Come on, give us 
a break! 
</P>
<P>
JERRY COWLE 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Palisades 
</P>
