<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. RESPONSE TO CIVIL WAR IN LIBERIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Your editorial ("Thinking the Unthinkable," July 31) suggested, "Yes, U.S. 
intervention in Liberia may be the best humanitarian move." 
</P>
<P>
Why United States troops? Where are the United Nations peacekeeping forces? 
Clearly this horrifying massacre of 600 women and children is a violation of 
the principles of the United Nations Charter. When are we going to impose 
compliance with the U.N. Charter and international law? We need an 
international force capable of preventing such massacres and a commander in 
chief who need not wait for the Security Council to debate the problem. 
</P>
<P>
EDWARD C. PERRY II 
</P>
<P>
Palm Springs 
</P>
</TEXT>
