<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEAT NEEDS A WIN TO MAKE PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHOENIX 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Heat needs one victory in its last two games to secure a 
playoff berth in the American Professional Soccer League West. 
</P>
<P>
The Heat (9-9, 70 points), enters tonight's 7:30 game against the host Arizona 
Condors in third place in the APSL West Southern Division. 
</P>
<P>
California (9-10, 80) and Real Santa Barbara (9-9, 75) lead the division. San 
Diego (8-11, 66), which plays host to Santa Barbara Saturday night at 7:30, has 
an outside chance for a playoff spot. California is at Santa Barbara on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Three teams qualify for the playoffs and only California has secured a spot. 
Postseason play begins next weekend with the second and third-place finishers 
playing a home and home series. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. finishes the regular season in Albuquerque, N.M., Saturday night against 
the New Mexico Chiles. 
</P>
