<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Keeping Cool at the Neighborhood Pool: Summer vacation is just about 
over for most Southern California youngsters, but there's still time to make a 
splash and beat the heat at the neighborhood swimming pool. As three young 
children sneak a peak through the fence surrounding the Carson Park pool 
recently, other youngsters attempt to dunk each other -- and avoid being 
dunked. And a diver appears to be flying, albeit upside down, as he does a 
double back-flip into the deep end. AXEL KOESTER / For The Times 
</P>
