<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peru Takes Drastic Economic Turn: Newly inaugurated President Alberto Fujimori, 
facing a devastated economy, inaugurated an economic austerity program that 
freed the monetary exchange rate, lifted price controls and raised the price of 
gasoline by nearly 3,000% to equal $1.12 a gallon. The government attempted to 
soften the blow to consumers by ordering wages increased 100% to a maximum of 
$125 a month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
