<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Companies Recall Electrical Converters, Toys: The Consumer Product Safety 
Commission said about 12,000 power transformers were being recalled because of 
possible hazards. 
</P>
<P>
They were imported from Taiwan and bore the labels "Rocket," "Seven Star," 
"Saiko" or "Step Up/Step Down." Four toys sold by House of Lloyd Inc. of 
Grandview, Mo., are being recalled because they present a choking hazard to 
young children. The toys, sold at home parties held by House of Lloyd 
salespeople, are the "Pull a Long Construction" train set; "Press N' Go Choo 
Choo," a plastic train, "June and Julie Musical Dolls" and "Motor Mouse." 
</P>
</TEXT>
