</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Government-Held Thrifts Lose $3.1 Billion: The first-quarter loss by savings 
and loans controlled by the government compared to a deficit of $6.4 billion in 
the previous quarter, the Resolution Trust Corp. said. The 350 thrifts under 
the government's conservatorship program reported operating losses of $1.4 
billion during the quarter ended March 31, a slight improvement from losses of 
$1.6 billion the previous three months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
