<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Soviet hockey federation said it plans to sue the Detroit Red Wings for 
signing forward Sergei Fedorov. 
</P>
<P>
Fedorov, one of the Soviet national team's top players, left the team July 21 
after a game against the United States at the Goodwill Games. 
</P>
<P>
The Red Wings announced two days later that Fedorov had agreed to a contract. 
</P>
<P>
Tass, the official Soviet news agency, said the Soviet hockey federation and 
the Soviet Army Club had decided to sue because Fedorov, 20, violated the 
Soviet labor code. 
</P>
