<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEAM TENNIS; 
</P>
<P>
STRINGS FINISH FAST, FINISH RACQUETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GARY KLEIN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Strings' strategy of saving their best for last paid off 
Thursday night in the TeamTennis Western Division final. 
</P>
<P>
Behind the play of John Lloyd and Robin White, the league's top-ranked mixed 
doubles team, the Strings defeated the defending champion San Antonio Racquets, 
24-18, before 775 at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
The Strings, making their first playoff appearance in six years, advanced to 
Sunday night's championship match at the Forum where they will meet the winner 
of tonight's Eastern Division final between the Raleigh Edge and the Miami 
Beach Breakers at Raleigh, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
San Antonio, which also won the league championship in 1986, missed the final 
for only the second time in five years. 
</P>
<P>
The Strings, who won the TeamTennis title in 1981 when Martina Navratilova was 
a member of the team, had a league-best 12-2 regular-season record and are 8-0 
at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
Because of that success, Lloyd, the Strings' player-coach, took advantage of a 
league rule that allows the home team to determine the order that the men's and 
women's singles, men's and women's doubles and mixed doubles matches will be 
played. 
</P>
<P>
"I thought about changing the order," said Lloyd, whose team lost its final 
regular-season match at San Antonio last Sunday. "But I thought, 'What the 
hell. If we can stay even until the last two sets, we'd have a great chance." 
</P>
<P>
The score was tied, 12-12, after three sets, before White defeated Elna 
Reinach, 6-3, to give the Strings an 18-15 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Lloyd and White defeated Sammy Giammalva and Reinach, 6-3, to secure the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
The Strings took command of the match early when Anne White and Robin White 
defeated Mary Lou Daniels and Reinach, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
San Antonio came back behind Giammalva, who took all but one point from Nick 
Brown in four games. Brown was replaced by Lloyd who lost the final two games 
in a 6-0 defeat. 
</P>
<P>
Lloyd and Brown defeated Giammalva and Dacio Campos, 6-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
