<TEXT>
<P>
What would seem an idea right out of "Mission Impossible" -- a one-hour 
recapitulation of last season's many plot twists on "Twin Peaks" -- has been 
canceled, ABC said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
ABC originally planned to air on Sept. 29 a show that would have recapped 
important points in the surreal saga of sex, murder and doughnuts in a small 
logging hamlet in Washington state. 
</P>
<P>
The series now is in summer repeats. 
</P>
<P>
But the network and the show's makers, Lynch-Frost Productions, mutually agreed 
to call off the special and concentrate all their energy on the show's second 
season, said ABC spokeswoman Janice Gretemeyer. 
</P>
<P>
"Twin Peaks" will begin its second season with a two-hour Sunday broadcast on 
Sept. 30, then appear regularly on Saturday nights. 
</P>
